	<div class="container">
		<p class="title">Guide</p><br>
		<div class="guide">
			<p class="guide-head">Users</p>
			<div class="guide-body">
				<ul>
					<li>Users can store and manage their health records on one place at anytime, from anywhere.</li>
					<li>During registration, we collect few personal informations like Address, Contact No, etc.
						which can be updated later.
						Based on these you will be provided a unique 6 digit health ID.</li>
					<li><strong>Health ID</strong> is unique number which helps to identify you as a user of this
						website. Once alloted Health ID cannot be changed.</li>
					<li>Additional medical details form is expected to be filled for better understanding about you.
					</li>
					<li>Everytime you visit a doctor, he/she will ask your <strong>Health ID</strong> and then be able
						to view all your past medical records and lab reports.</li>
					<li>This helps Doctors understand your health in a better way.</li>
					<li>Doctors only can add a new treatment record.</li>
					<li>You can view all your current on going medical treatment records from the <strong>Current
							Treatments</strong> tab.
					<li>On completion of your treatment, either you or the concern Doctor only can end the treatment.
					</li>
					<li>Once the treatment is terminated it will be transfered to <strong>Previous Treatments</strong>
						tab.</li>
					<li>Lab Reports can be send by the concern Laboratory to your database.</li>
					<li>Treatment specific lab reports will be mentioned in the Treatment details.</li>
					<li>All the reports can be downloaded from <strong>Lab Reports</strong> tab.</li>
					<li>User can have a one to one chat with their specific Doctors from the <strong>Chat</strong> tab.
					</li>
					<li><strong>Settings</strong> tab is to manage your profile details and other informations.</li>

			</div>
		</div>
		<hr>
		<div class="guide">
			<p class="guide-head">Doctors</p>
			<div class="guide-body">
				<ul>
					<li>Doctors can manage their patient records online from anywhere.</li>
					<li>In order to sign-up as a Doctor, you need to provide your personal, professional information
						along with a MCIR No.</li>
					<li>Once registered you will be able to use the services of this website.</li>
					<li>From the <strong>Home</strong> tab, you can search for a patient by <strong>Health ID</strong>.
					</li>
					<li>Then you can view all medical records & reports of the patient and can create a new treatment.
					</li>
					<li>All your on going treated pateint records can be found in <strong>Current Patients</strong> tab.
					</li>
					<li>Once terminated by either of you, it will be added to <strong>Previous Patients</strong> tab.
					</li>
					<li>You can have a chat with your current patients from <strong>Chat</strong> tab.</li>
					<li><strong>Settings</strong> tab can help you to manage your profile and settings.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
		<hr>
		<div class="guide">
			<p class="guide-head">Laboratory</p>
			<div class="guide-body">
				<ul>
					<li>Laboratories can register themselves on this portal by providing few informations.</li>
					<li>From <strong>Home</strong> tab, you can search for patient by Health ID and submit a lab report
						to them.</li>
					<li>We have different section for treatment specific report and general report. Submit them
						accordingly.</li>
					<li>All your sent reports will be visible in <strong>Sent Reports</strong> tab.</li>
					<li><strong>Settings</strong> tab will help you to manage your profile and other settings.</li>
				</ul>

			</div>
